feed.title: Dispelling the Myth: K&F Growth Acquisition Corp. II Warrants and the Fictional $100 Price Target
feed.summary: This article debunks the myth that K&F Growth Acquisition Corp. II (NASDAQ: KFIIU) issued equity warrants with a $100 price target, clarifying that no warrants were part of its IPO. It highlights the dangers of financial misinformation and urges investors to rely on official company filings and reputable sources. The company's future performance hinges on its ability to successfully complete a business combination within the experiential entertainment sector.

feed.title: Ogier provides Cayman expertise on four Nasdaq IPOs, reflecting ‘buoyant’ SPAC market
feed.summary: Ogier's Corporate team in the Cayman Islands acted as legal counsel for four recent Nasdaq IPOs, raising over US$700 million. Three of these were Special Purpose Acquisition Companies (SPACs), highlighting a robust SPAC market in 2025. This activity underscores Ogier's expertise in facilitating the establishment and listing of Cayman Islands companies on US exchanges.
